The paper deals with the problem of improving accuracy in private data analysis while preserving privacy, which is a central concern in the field of computer security (cs.CR). The techniques proposed involve manipulating and analyzing databases, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of statistical metrics such as mean, median, and variance, which are relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and databases (cs.DB).
